post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_5766006_5766015_0": {"length": 8, "quality": 0.8888888888888888, "section_id": 3342}}, "n3337": {"so_5766006_5766015_0": {"length": 8, "quality": 0.8888888888888888, "section_id": 3212}}, "n4659": {"so_5766006_5766015_0": {"length": 7, "quality": 0.7777777777777778, "section_id": 7674}}}, "5766006": {"ViewCount": "442", "Body": "<p>What does C++ standard say should happen for the following code when there is no pending exception being processed higher up the stack?</p>\n<pre><code>try {\n  throw;\n} catch (...) {\n  cerr &lt;&lt; \"Caught exception.\" &lt;&lt; endl;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Will the throw with no object be caught or not?</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "5766015", "Title": "Does catch (...) work on throw; with no object?", "CreationDate": "2011-04-23T18:17:17.720", "Id": "5766006", "CommentCount": "0", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastActivityDate": "2011-04-23T18:19:33.020", "Score": "4", "OwnerUserId": "115751", "Tags": "<c++><exception><try-catch><throw><ellipsis>", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "5766015": {"Id": "5766015", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>From the 2003 C++ Standard \u00a715.1[except.throw]/8:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_5766006_5766015_0\">If  no  exception  is  presently  being  handled,  executing  a  <em>throw-expression</em>  with  no  operand  calls <code>terminate()</code>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>So, in your example, since no exception is currently being handled, nothing is thrown and instead <code>terminate()</code> is called.  Since <code>terminate()</code> does not return, your <code>catch</code> block will never be entered.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2011-04-23T18:19:33.020", "CommentCount": "3", "CreationDate": "2011-04-23T18:19:33.020", "ParentId": "5766006", "Score": "12", "OwnerUserId": "151292"}});